msgctxt "0000"
msgid "I love adventure..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0001"
msgid "I guess."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "talk_0001"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Ugh, why do some people equate the\n"
"unnecessary pursuit of power with\n"
"some childish dream of adventure?\n"
"That sword may be good for slaying\n"
"monsters, sure, but it's not like a\n"
"sword alone makes a hero. Ya know?<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk_0002"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Huh?<2.pa> Oh, I guess you did venture all the\n"
"way out to a stable in the mountains,\n"
"didn't you..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk_0003"
msgid ""
"<1.so>If the <2.se_co>sword that seals the darkness<3.re_co>\n"
"or whatever it's called really exists...\n"
"\n"
"I hope a kind swordsman like you will be\n"
"the one to wield it."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk_1000"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I've got to clean while it's still dark...\n"
"Must clean..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: raw
msgctxt "talk_2000"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Welcome to <2.se_co>Snowfield Stable<3.re_co>!<4.ra>If you're "
"planning to head deeper into\n"
"the snow, I recommend resting in one\n"
"of our soft beds first."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk_5000"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I overheard what you and Danton were\n"
"talking about.\n"
"\n"
"I can't do much to help, but...I'll keep\n"
"this stable clean and tidy, so please\n"
"come rest here when you need to."
msgstr ""

